  "texts": [
    "That is, a public knowledge probability distribution function ('public pdf') is generated by gathering the nsam p = 100 most recent samples foot_4 and generating an estimate of the truth using kernel density estimation.",
    "The distance between the public pdf and the truth provides a shorthand for the general welfare of a society.",
    "We define knowledge collapse as occurring where there is a large and increasing distance between the public and true pdfs as a result of the collapse of tail regions and increasing mass near the mean.",
    "The individual's payoff is calculated according to the distance they move the public pdf towards the true pdf.",
    "That is, the innovation (individual payoff) I generated by an individuals additional (n + 1)th sample is calculated with respect to the true pdf p true (x) and the current public pdf p public (x), based on the Hellinger distance H(p(x), q(x)) foot_5, as follows:"
  ]
}